Questions
========================================================
- Who has programming experience in any language?
- Who has a statistics background?
- Who has previously worked with R/RStudio?
- Which limitations should be concerned while using the T-Test?
- Is there a useful graphical representation for common descritive statistics
  for two groups of observations at once?
- Can the model $\hat y = \beta_2 \cdot sin(\beta_1\cdot x_1) + \beta_0$ be called a linear one?
- What is "literate programming"?


Getting started
========================================================

Look at the Github repository:
https://github.com/arbox/IQLA-GIAT-Summer-School

Go to the menu `File > New Project > Version Control > Git`

and try to dowload the existing project from Github.

